<chapter id="formtags">

    <para>

        These tags can be used in a jsp file to display....??!??

    </para>

    <example>
        <title>Usage on GS Tags</title>
        <screen>
<![CDATA[<%@ taglib uri="/portletWidgets" prefix="gs" %>
<%@ taglib uri="/portletAPI" prefix="portletAPI" %>
<portletAPI:init/>]]>
        </screen>
    </example>



    <title>Formtags</title>
    <para>

    </para>

    <sect1 id="parameters">
        <title>Parameters</title>

            <title>Tagattributes</title>

            <table>
                <title>attributes of tags</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>attributename</entry><entry>description</entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>name</entry><entry>string: name of the tag</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>value</entry><entry>string: value of the tag</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>size</entry><entry>integer: size of the field</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>maxlength</entry><entry>integer: maximal length of the field</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>disabled</entry><entry>boolean: if the element is disabled</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>readonly</entry><entry>boolean: if the element is readonly</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>checked</entry><entry>boolean: if the element is selected</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>bean</entry><entry>string: name of the corresponding bean</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>

            To most of the tags you can pass in a name of the bean you saved from your java file (see down for
            an example).
    </sect1>

    <!-- ================================================================ -->

    <sect1 id="tags">
        <title>Tags</title>

        <sect2 id="actiontag">
            <title>ActionLink</title>
            <para>
                This tag creates an actionlink pointing to the same portlet with additional parameters.
            </para>
            <table>
                <title>Attributes to actionlink</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>label</entry><entry>action</entry> <entry>bean (ActionLinkBean)</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>

            <example>
                <title>Usage of actionlink</title>
                <screen>
<![CDATA[<gs:actionlink label="mylabel" action="name=hallo"/>]]>
                </screen>
                This example would create an html href pointing to the current portlet with a clickable
                text mylabel and a paramter/value pair name/hallo. Alternativly you could use an
                actionlinkbean (see actionlinkbean) to pass into this tag.
            </example>
        </sect2>


        <sect2 id="checkboxtag">
            <title>CheckBox</title>
            <para>
                This tag shows a checkbox.
            </para>
            <table>
                <title>Attributes to checkbox</title>
                <tgroup cols="4">
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>name</entry><entry>value</entry><entry>checked</entry><entry>disabled</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>bean (CheckBoxBean)</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <example>
                <title>Usage of checkbox</title>
                <screen>
<![CDATA[<gs:checkbox name="name" value="value" checked="true" disabled="false"/>]]>
                </screen>
                This creates a selected checkbox with the name 'name' and the value 'value'.
            </example>
        </sect2>

        <sect2 id="formtag">
            <title>Form</title>
            <para>
                This tag is used to surround a form.
            </para>
            <example>
                <title>Usage of form</title>
                <screen>
<![CDATA[<gs:form action="identifier">
...
</gs:form>]]>
                </screen>
            </example>
        </sect2>

        <sect2 id="fileinputtag">
            <title>FileInput</title>
        </sect2>


        <sect2 id="passwordfieldtag">
            <title>PasswordField</title>
            <para>
                This tag renders a passwordfield.
            </para>
            <table>
                <title>Attributes to passwordfield</title>
                <tgroup cols="4">
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>name</entry><entry>value</entry><entry>size</entry><entry>disabled</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>maxlength</entry><entry>bean (PasswordBean)</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <example>
                <title>Usage of passwordfield</title>
                <screen>
<![CDATA[<gs:password name="password" value="" size="15"/>]]>
                </screen>
                This example creates a password field with the name password, no default value and a size of 15 characters.
            </example>
        </sect2>


        <sect2 id="radiobuttontag">
            <title>RadioButton</title>
            <para>
                This tag shows a radiobutton. You can group multiple radiobuttons simple by giving
                the radiobuttons the same name. see radiobuttonlist.
            </para>
            <table>
                <title>Attributes to radiobutton</title>
                <tgroup cols="4">
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>name</entry><entry>value</entry><entry>checked</entry><entry>disabled</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>bean (RadioButtonBean)</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <example>
                <title>Usage of radiobutton</title>
                <screen>
<![CDATA[<gs:radiobutton name="name" value="value" checked="true" disabled="false"/>]]>
                </screen>
                This creates a selected radiobutton woth the name 'name' and the value 'value'.
            </example>
        </sect2>

        <sect2 id="submitbuttontag">
            <title>SubmitButton</title>
        </sect2>


        <sect2 id="textareatag">
            <title>TextArea</title>
            <para>
                This tag creates a textarea.
            </para>
            <table>
                <title>Attributes to textarea</title>
                <tgroup cols="4">
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>name</entry><entry>value</entry><entry>readonly</entry><entry>disabled</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>bean (TextAreaBean)</entry><entry>cols</entry><entry>rows</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <example>
                <title>Usage of textarea</title>
                <screen>
<![CDATA[<gs:textarea name="inputfield" value="This is text" rows="120" cols="30"  disabled="false" />]]>
                </screen>
                This creates a 120x30 textinputfield with the name 'inputfield' and the text 'This is text'.
            </example>
        </sect2>

        <sect2 id="textfieldtag">
            <title>TextField</title>
            <para>
                This tag shows a textinputfield.
            </para>
            <table>
                <title>Attributes to textfield</title>
                <tgroup cols="4">
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>name</entry><entry>value</entry><entry>size</entry><entry>disabled</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>maxlength</entry><entry>bean (TextFieldBean)</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <example>
                <title>Usage of textfield</title>
                <screen>
<![CDATA[<gs:textfield name="textfield" value="" size="15"/>]]>
                </screen>
                This example creates a input field with the name textfield, no default value and a size of 15 characters.
            </example>
        </sect2>


        <sect2 id="texttag">
            <title>Text</title>
            <para>
                This tag shows text.
            </para>
            <table>
                <title>Attributes to text</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>text</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <example>
                <title>Usage of text</title>
                <screen>
<![CDATA[<gs:text text="text"/>]]>
                </screen>
            </example>
        </sect2>


        <sect2 id="labeltag">
            <title>Label</title>
            <para>
                This tag shows a label.
            </para>
            <table>
                <title>Attributes to label</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>text</entry><entry>bean (LabelBean)</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <example>
                <title>Usage of label</title>
                <screen>
<![CDATA[<gs:text text="label"/>]]>
                </screen>
            </example>
            This example creates a label with the text 'label'.
        </sect2>


        <sect2 id="dropdownlist">
            <title>DropDownList</title>
            <para>
                This tag creates a dropdownlist. You need to pass in a see dropdownlistbean.
            </para>
            <table>
                <title>Attributes to dropdownlist</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>bean (DropDownListBean)</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <example>
                <title>Usage of dropdownlist</title>
                <screen>
<![CDATA[<gs:dropdownlist  bean="name of dropdownlistbean"/>]]>
                </screen>
                This example creates a dropdownlist from the bean.
            </example>
        </sect2>


        <sect2 id="listbox">
            <title>ListBox</title>
            <para>
                This tag creates a listbox. You need to pass in a see listboxbean.
            </para>
            <table>
                <title>Attributes to listbox</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>bean (ListBoxBean)</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <example>
                <title>Usage of listbox</title>
                <screen>
<![CDATA[<gs:listbox  bean="name of listboxbean"/>]]>
                </screen>
                This example creates a listbox from the bean.
            </example>
        </sect2>


        <sect2 id="checkboxlist">
            <title>CheckBoxList</title>
            <para>
                This tag creates a list of checkboxes with associated labels.  You need to pass in a see checkboxlistbean.
            </para>
            <table>
                <title>Attributes to checkboxlist</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>bean (CheckBoxListBean)</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <example>
                <title>Usage of checkboxlist</title>
                <screen>
<![CDATA[<gs:checkboxlist  bean="name of checkboxlistbean"/>]]>
                </screen>
                This example creates a list of checkboxes (with labels) from the bean.
            </example>
        </sect2>


        <sect2 id="radiobuttonlist">
            <title>RadioButtonList</title>
            <para>
                This tag creates a list of radiobuttons with associated labels.
            </para>
            <table>
                <title>Attributes to radiobuttonlist</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>bean (RadioButtonListBean)</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <example>
                <title>Usage of radiobuttonlist</title>
                <screen>
<![CDATA[<gs:checkboxlist  bean="name of radiobuttonlistbean"/>]]>
                </screen>
                This creates a list of radiobuttons (with labels) from the bean.
            </example>
        </sect2>


    </sect1>

